    {
      "id": "0a9f04cc8a80b4b44b4bb46c1ec29ccd9a3c4073",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-08 00:06:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nI don't think this is proper use of an Obsoletes.  It especially strange to say that this is obsoleting the lustre-client package name and then turn around an offer exactly the same package name.\n\nThis is exactly the reason that the separate \"lustre-client\" packages should not exists, though.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "97ac3f3b624338376ee4fa55dce3505601cbd211",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-08 00:08:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThis will definitely be a problem if we want to have a lustre-client subpackage generated from the main lustre build in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "b4691d4f32d7504c1fa1a63581c84438b7e92325",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-08 04:24:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThe use of Obsoletes is consistent with the kernel.spec file:\n\n Obsoletes: kernel-headers\n Provides: kernel-headers = %{version}\n\nand also the RHEL-6/7 e2fsprogs.spec file:\n\n Obsoletes: e4fsprogs < %{version}-%{release}\n Provides: e4fsprogs = %{version}-%{release}\n\nI think it makes sense to limit this to Obsolete lustre-client of the current or earlier releases so that it would not cause problems with future packages:\n\n Obsoletes: lustre-client <= %{version}-%{release}\n Provides: lustre-client = %{version}-%{release}\n\nthough if/when we split into separate lustre and lustre-client packages the \"Obsoletes:\" part would be removed.\n\nRunning rpmlint on the current lustre.spec file complains about \"unversioned-explicit-obsoletes\" and \"unversioned-explicit-provides\", so this definitely seems like something that the RPM .spec is intended to contain.\n\nI'll fix those issues and a few more that rpmlint is complaining about and re-push the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "e6f6be8cf2f12d3ea5e0d63ce9f56c4f1174af4a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-08 20:22:44.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 5.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "80e9f0f3b6f189d52a094d7a5b899b4d968a37e9",
